      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:7:3:4",
      "text": [
        " لَا تُكْثِرْ مِنْ شُرْبِ الْمَاءِ فَإِنَّهُ مَادَّةٌ لِكُلِّ دَاءٍ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Sahl Bin Ziyad, from Ali Bin Hassan, from Musa Bin Bakr, from one of our companions, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Do not frequent from drinking the water for it extends every illness’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "4. A number of our people have narrated from Sahl ibn Ziyad from Ali ibn Hassan from Musa ibn Bakr from certain persons of our people who have said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Do not drink water excessively, it is the substance of every illness.’” "
        ]
      }
